cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper discusses the development of convolutional neural networks for image segmentation tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of the principle of equivariance to symmetry transformations also suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning (cs.LG), as well as neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the implementation of these networks on manifolds suggests a potential connection to geometric deep learning (cs.GR).
